verbs.description: imbreathe (third-person singular simple present imbreathes, present participle imbreathing, simple past and past participle imbreathed)

examples: Alighting some graceful exotic bird from the captivity of a dingy cage, Lady Parvula de Panzoust hovered a moment before the portal as much to manipulate her draperies, it seemed, as to imbreathe the soft sweet air.
